Jamba Ward normally receives 5-stars from us, however,  this time we were disappointed when we went there a couple of HOURS before their stated closing time only to find locked doors, chairs turned over on the table, and workers looking at us as they went along their business. Maybe the franchisee owner should be told about our disappointment and wasted time???   Would give us hope for the future positive and enjoyable experiences.

Nothing beats a nice icy cold drink on a hot summer day! My favorites are the classic Mango-a-go-go and the Acai Antioxidant, both are very delicious and not too creamy! It's the perfect treat when you're forced to sweat out a river on a hot day, it will cool you right down. I just wish they have drive through for those times when they're busy and is hard to find parking next to the store. It doesn't help that there's a Starbucks next door too, even more so it's hard to find parking close to the stores.

Walked in at 3:45pm on 9/1/19. 3 employees working on orders. No one at register. Totally ignored. One order was made. Customer called came up. No one serviced me. Walked out and went to Ohana Marketplace where as soon as I got to the counter I was serviced.
Great service! Cashier was friendly and drink was ready in literally just a couple minutes.

I HAVE been to other Jambas where the service was a lot faster, so they are not exactly the fastest, but they're definitely not slow either. Good service, good location, love Jamba!
